These older years are practically non-existent on the Bordeaux market. To obtain wines of this age and calibre is akin to seeking out a Cezanne or Matisse. We know of no wine merchant anywhere who can offer his clientele clarets of this age and calibre and rarity. In most instances, if one is fortunate to find it in Bordeaux at all, the cost would probably be higher than the prices at which we are offering these wines. Obviously, they are subject to prior sale and, generally speaking, are irreplaceable. We recommend acquisi-
